            <notesStmt>
                <note type="summary">
                    
                        
                            
                            <p>A letter from Thomas Patrick Gill (1858-1931) to Sir Matthew Nathan (1862-1939). In the letter Gill states the he is transmitting statements of the movements of the department's staff between 22 April and 1 May, the week of the Easter Rising. Gill adds that it was not possible to contact all members of staff and any further statements will be sent on later.</p>
                            
                        
                            
                        
                            
                            <p>Sir Matthew Nathan was the under-secretary for Ireland from 1914 to 1916. In 1916 Nathan offered his resignation following the outbreak of the Easter Rising. Gill served as the secretary for the Department of Agriculture and Technical Instruction from its establishment in 1900 until 1923.</p>
                            
                        
                    
                </note>
